# Cloudflare Pages routing rules.
#
# /r/:id  →  /r.html?id=:id   (server-side rewrite, NOT a redirect — URL bar
#                              stays at /r/<hash>, but Pages serves r.html)
#
# Status 200 = rewrite/proxy semantics; status 301/302/308 would visibly
# redirect and break shareable links. The `:splat` token captures whatever
# is in the wildcard segment.
#
# Used by site/r.html (the read-only audit results page) so users can share
# advocatemcp.com/r/abc123 without seeing the .html or query-string in
# their browser.

/r/*  /r.html?id=:splat  200

# /mcp.html → /mcp-server  (marketing page rename, May 7 2026)
#
# The marketing page was originally at site/mcp.html. Cloudflare Pages
# auto-strips .html and serves it at /mcp — but the Worker registers a
# route on /mcp for the MCP JSON-RPC server (used by Claude Desktop /
# Cursor / other MCP clients), so the marketing page was unreachable on
# the apex domain: every request to /mcp got the JSON server response.
#
# Fix: rename the file to mcp-server.html (Pages serves at /mcp-server)
# and 301 the legacy /mcp.html URL here so any inbound link or bookmark
# still resolves. We canNOT redirect /mcp itself from this file — Pages
# never sees /mcp because the Worker intercepts at the edge before Pages
# routing runs.
#
# Out of scope of this rule:
#   - /mcp                  → still served by the Worker (MCP JSON-RPC)
#   - api.advocatemcp.com/mcp  → unchanged, canonical for MCP clients
/mcp.html  /mcp-server  301
